Before Ashley started a three-hour drive, her car's odometer reading was $ 29792$, a palindrome. At her destination, the odometer reading was another palindrome. If Ashley never exceeded the speed limit of $ 75$ miles per hour, which of the following was her greatest possible average speed?\\
\\
$ \textbf{(A)}\  33\frac 13 \qquad \textbf{(B)}\  53\frac 13\qquad \textbf{(C)}\  60\frac 23\qquad \textbf{(D)}\  70\frac 13\qquad \textbf{(E)}\ 74\frac 13$
